  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across 5 flow-speed combinations. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels are compared against required levels driven by MRL 5. Methodology follows the power-law hemolysis scalar approach described in the literature (see referencesIdentifier). Decision: Accepted subject to post-market surveillance commitments.",
