      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in validation simulations must be shown to be equivalent to those in the COU simulations; any differences must be quantified and their effect on hemolysis index bounded.",
      "rationale": "Rotational speed and flow rate are matched between validation and COU simulations. Inlet velocity profile differs: validation uses a developed pipe-flow profile while COU uses a patient-specific atrial flow profile. The effect of this difference on hemolysis index has not been quantified."
